metadata.name: No Writing on Walls #6
metadata.description:
"No Writing on Walls," is a visual representation of the concept of writing on walls as a form of self-expression. The abstract wall covered in graffiti and positive words serves to showcase the diverse voices and messages that people want to share, despite the restriction against writing on walls. My aim was to challenge the negative stereotypes associated with graffiti and demonstrate the beauty and creativity that can arise when people are allowed to express themselves freely. With this artwork, I hope to spark reflection and encourage viewers to consider the power of self-expression and its impact on individuals and society.
- Look for the gold mode
- press p so export png
- press s to export svg

metadata.name: paintflow #43
metadata.description:
For this project, I wanted to try out Ty Vek's SVG technique for creating gen art. I used some basic SVG filters to achieve the paint brush effect, then just added some simple line and curve patterns. The result is quite nice and organic feeling! There are only 2 colors: red and black - I felt it was important to focus on the shapes and lines rather than the colors. The number of curves varies from 2 to 4, and each can be filled above or below. That's the gist of it! I hope you get some pretty pieces.

You can save the generated SVG by pressing the 's' key, and you can save a PNG version by pressing the 'p' key.

Please enjoy!

metadata.name: Forgive Your Sins #3
metadata.description:
This is a colorful remix for #genuary32nd of my late #genuary23 work done on 31st of January!
This is my tribute to Yayoi Kusama (#genuary25) with viscous dots of digital ink thrown in digital liquid and then shaken by digital sine waves (#genuary15) inspired by marbling techniques.

This is the 2nd iteration of my Wasm/Rust fluid simulation engine after "Viscous Circles" collection. Check it on FxHash if you want to know more about the engine behind this generator.

Controls

You can stop at any step if you like the state at this instant, you can restart it, de/increase resolution (default is 4096x4096 to have sharp image, up to 16K x 16K) and snapshot at any resolution.

- H: hide/show help.
- Space - pause/start animation.
- R - restart animation.
- I - hide/show res/fps panel.
- A-Q/D - down/up full resolution
- S - take full resolution snapshot

Now, forgive your sins!

Forgive Your Sins @naibdian 2023 Project made using Opensource WebGL, WASM/Rust/JS libs
#genuary32nd #genuary23 #genuary15 #genuary25
